#: ../../changelog.rst:176
msgid ""
"Implement the `URI options specification`_ in the "
":meth:`~pymongo.mongo_client.MongoClient` constructor. Consequently, "
"there are a number of changes in connection options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:180
msgid "The ``tlsInsecure`` option has been added."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:181
msgid ""
"The ``tls`` option has been added. The older ``ssl`` option has been "
"retained as an alias to the new ``tls`` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:183
msgid "``wTimeout`` has been deprecated in favor of ``wTimeoutMS``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:184
msgid "``wTimeoutMS`` now overrides ``wTimeout`` if the user provides both."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:185
msgid "``j`` has been deprecated in favor of ``journal``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:186
msgid "``journal`` now overrides ``j`` if the user provides both."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:187
msgid ""
"``ssl_cert_reqs`` has been deprecated in favor of "
"``tlsAllowInvalidCertificates``. Instead of ``ssl.CERT_NONE``, "
"``ssl.CERT_OPTIONAL`` and ``ssl.CERT_REQUIRED``, the new option expects a"
" boolean value - ``True`` is equivalent to ``ssl.CERT_NONE``, while "
"``False`` is equivalent to ``ssl.CERT_REQUIRED``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:191
msgid ""
"``ssl_match_hostname`` has been deprecated in favor of "
"``tlsAllowInvalidHostnames``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:192
msgid "``ssl_ca_certs`` has been deprecated in favor of ``tlsCAFile``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:193
msgid ""
"``ssl_certfile`` has been deprecated in favor of "
"``tlsCertificateKeyFile``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:194
msgid ""
"``ssl_pem_passphrase`` has been deprecated in favor of "
"``tlsCertificateKeyFilePassword``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:195
msgid ""
"``waitQueueMultiple`` has been deprecated without replacement. This "
"option was a poor solution for putting an upper bound on queuing since it"
" didn't affect queuing in other parts of the driver."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:198
msgid ""
"The ``retryWrites`` URI option now defaults to ``True``. Supported write "
"operations that fail with a retryable error will automatically be retried"
" one time, with at-most-once semantics."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:201
msgid ""
"Support for retryable reads and the ``retryReads`` URI option which is "
"enabled by default. See the :class:`~pymongo.mongo_client.MongoClient` "
"documentation for details. Now that supported operations are retried "
"automatically and transparently, users should consider adjusting any "
"custom retry logic to prevent an application from inadvertently retrying "
"for too long."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:207
msgid "Support zstandard for wire protocol compression."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:208
msgid ""
"Support for periodically polling DNS SRV records to update the mongos "
"proxy list without having to change client configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:210
msgid ""
"New method :meth:`pymongo.database.Database.aggregate` to support running"
" database level aggregations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:212
msgid ""
"Support for publishing Connection Monitoring and Pooling events via the "
"new :class:`~pymongo.monitoring.ConnectionPoolListener` class. See "
":mod:`~pymongo.monitoring` for an example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:215
msgid ""
":meth:`pymongo.collection.Collection.aggregate` and "
":meth:`pymongo.database.Database.aggregate` now support the ``$merge`` "
"pipeline stage and use read preference "
":attr:`~pymongo.read_preferences.ReadPreference.PRIMARY` if the ``$out`` "
"or ``$merge`` pipeline stages are used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:220
msgid ""
"Support for specifying a pipeline or document in "
":meth:`~pymongo.collection.Collection.update_one`, "
":meth:`~pymongo.collection.Collection.update_many`, "
":meth:`~pymongo.collection.Collection.find_one_and_update`, "
":meth:`~pymongo.operations.UpdateOne`, and "
":meth:`~pymongo.operations.UpdateMany`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:226
msgid "New BSON utility functions :func:`~bson.encode` and :func:`~bson.decode`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:227
msgid ""
":class:`~bson.binary.Binary` now supports any bytes-like type that "
"implements the buffer protocol."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:229
msgid ""
"Resume tokens can now be accessed from a ``ChangeStream`` cursor using "
"the :attr:`~pymongo.change_stream.ChangeStream.resume_token` attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:231
msgid ""
"Connections now survive primary step-down when using MongoDB 4.2+. "
"Applications should expect less socket connection turnover during replica"
" set elections."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:237
msgid ""
"Applications that use MongoDB with the MMAPv1 storage engine must now "
"explicitly disable retryable writes via the connection string (e.g. "
"``MongoClient(\"mongodb://my.mongodb.cluster/db?retryWrites=false\")``) "
"or the :class:`~pymongo.mongo_client.MongoClient` constructor's keyword "
"argument (e.g. ``MongoClient(\"mongodb://my.mongodb.cluster/db\", "
"retryWrites=False)``) to avoid running into "
":class:`~pymongo.errors.OperationFailure` exceptions during write "
"operations. The MMAPv1 storage engine is deprecated and does not support "
"retryable writes which are now turned on by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:245
msgid ""
"In order to ensure that the ``connectTimeoutMS`` URI option is honored "
"when connecting to clusters with a ``mongodb+srv://`` connection string, "
"the minimum required version of the optional ``dnspython`` dependency has"
" been bumped to 1.16.0. This is a breaking change for applications that "
"use PyMongo's SRV support with a version of ``dnspython`` older than "
"1.16.0."
msgstr ""

